caption: Great Italian Market with delicious sandwiches, paninis, salads, Gelato, etc. On Fridays they have the best meatball sub you ever ate. Staff are pleasant and helpful. Highly recommended!
Amazing deli. Great sandwiches. Super friendly.  Reasonably priced. A hidden gem. Also a terrific stop for a "foodie". Unique Italian pastas, sauces and special cheeses.
Best little Italian joint in frederick and the best hoagies in town.

We ordered the Vignola and muffuletta subs today. These were absolutely the best subs we've ever had!  I will never order another sub from anywhere else! Ingredients were so fresh. Outstanding. Can't wait to order again!
Forza Italia 🇮🇹 ! Amazing subs, Limoncello Gelato is ridiculously addictive 😋
Tremendous and I mean tremendous sandwiches. Great people and quality.

Heard about this place from so many others on Frederick dine in and take out groups on Facebook and finally tried it. I got the Italian panini and it was the best panini I’ve ever had. They give you so much meat in it too.  Normally it comes with pesto but she replaced it with pesto mayo because they were out and it was just divine!
Delicious Italian sandwiches.
Great sandwiches, nice people.
Whenever I'm in downtown Frederick, Juliet's is a must stop. Delicious and generous sandwiches, and a great selection of authentic Italian foods and staples.
Meatball sub is to die for only had two so far because it's only a Friday special but worth the wait I'm in love
I absolutely love Juliet's. The whole family makes me feel just as much as family...I love Miss Juliet and Mike and Sara and Val y'all are all amazing. The food is amazing!!!
Nice place right in town. Very good subs. I've heard from others that all their food is good.
A top scene for Italian food. It was so delicious. Really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, I'll be back.

Juliet's Italian Market is not a bodega or a sudo store  named fancy to hide subpar delicacies. This is the gem of Frederick every Friday hot gooey Meatball subs come from out of her domain,inside is tight, but it's what I remembered from my time in Italy lots of baked goods and gelatos ,salads and more . If you are looking for a true Italian experience with authentic mouth watering dishes, ingredients and wares this is as about Usa authentic as it comes oh special tip call ahead for your order on Friday the Meatball's sell out quick Love you Juliet 💖 and thanks for the years of warm and filling memories
Delicious!
The place offers a vast range of delicious food. I enjoy eating here. The employees are always super nice, prices are reasonable and the place is always neat.

Great Italian sandwich shop & market! You can call in am order for curbside pickup or you can walk in and place an order. They also have a market section with pasta, etc and pre-made items (ravioli, meatballs, etc) and deserts (tiaramisu, microns, brownies).

Use to go to Vignoli’s before this and stopped in Juliette to take a sandwich home. The prosciutto and fresh mozzarella was delicious. Friendly service. Sandwich was well made and amply full of meat and cheese. Toppings nice too. Non appetit
Excellent sandwiches
Very yummy
I used to work here before Julia purchased the market, and she’s only made things better
Great subs, very nice people
Fresh, incredible food!
The meatball sub is only available on Fridays but it is worth the wait.
I love the muffuletta and everyone is so nice.  Great shop.
Great Food! The Meatball sub was incredible! Great service! They were very nice! You have to check them out
Fresh bread!  Coldcut subs da bomb!  Call ahead, they are busy for a reason.
Amazing cold cut sub, honestly the best I've ever had
Just had an absolutely amazing pastrami sandwich. Don't forget the Dream Bomba for dessert! Definitely worth the trip!
I got a whole shopping trip here and everything was wonderful! Even made me fresh mozzarella!! Sandwiches are delicious!

This spot is my favored. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I  constantly return again and again. The team is very helpful and the cuisine they place on your table is so delicious. I would always prefer to have a nice dinner here. I recommend this place with pleasure.
The service was great and so was my sandwich I had the ham and cheddar panini with spinach tomatoes and red onions and chipotle mayo on ciabatta bread. 😋
The staff has consistently been super friendly and their food tastes really good! You get so much food for a great price. Strongly recommend getting the cuban if you go!

The muffeleta sandwich was delicious! It would have been next level with a little italian seasoning and oil/vinegar. The food is the only reason I didnt give one star. There were only two people waiting on food yet it took 20 minutes to get our two sandwiches. The girls working behind the counter were so slow!! They were busy complaining and cursing rather than focusing on making food. I mentioned on my way out that I was disappointed in the service and I got yelled at, rather than an apology. Won't be back.
I had an amazing  in this restaurant. We liked the fantastic ambience and the food. The staff members are very attentive. I’m happy we finally decided to visit here.
Sandwiches are fantastic. Recommend.
The food is incredible
This is a great little market to get a sandwich and a nice Lavazza coffee.  This is a nice corner store like we had in the old days!
Fresh ingredients always win, best subs in town!
Everything here is made with care and love. The food is just fantastic!

Recently split the California and it was great - fresh tomato, avocado, turkey, and mozzarella. The bread was a delicious highlight - but I don't think it had a single shake of seasoning. Salt? Pepper? Something. Would have made it next level.  Also ordered a cannoli, which was tasty.

This place makes the best sandwiches in Frederick in my opinion. They have subs, panini, and traditional. The portions are big you could easily split a sandwich between two people or stuff yourself like I do. The service can be slow you need a bit of patience in this place. But you are rewarded.
The food is delicious and they make everything fresh.

Best sandwiches in Frederick by far, and that's saying something because Frederick is a world renowned sandwich town. Juliet is awesome and friendly and Michelle (the one with the tattoos) makes such good sandwiches that I actually married her.
Very good,
You'll find unexpected italian products you won't find anywhere else for miles.

Great littel Italian market I got the muffuletta sandwich and it was vary good it was made with fresh sliced meat and cheese I would definitely recommend it and the staff was super frendly i will be going back in the future

Some of the best sandwiches and subs in town and they are generous sizes. Specials are always worth trying. Check out some of the homemade items to go as well. It's a small place and they can get busy, so you'll sometimes have to wait a little bit, but it is worth it.
It's the real deal. I'd move to Frederick just for their mozzarella. And their pesto and homemade bread also amazing.
Great gelato! The chocolate hazelnut and strawberry
Love this place every time we go. Such fresh bread and amazing sandwiches
Fabulous Italian deli and grocery. Sandwich counter and prepared foods does brisk business at lunch time, and it's the perfect place to get hard-to-find ingredients for an Italian dinner.
Very nice little itialian sandwich shop & market, conveniently located on church st.

Food was great I loved everything! but the help someone named  Michelle terribly rude  and unprofessional. I was going to recommend this pace to everyone I know, but if she is the type of people they employ?! I’d take your business to any of the other great places downtown why pay more for extremely rude service
Great little shop. Real Italian products. Try the pepperoni in the deli case! Fabulous!
The service, the food and the ambiance is awesome. I will come back soon!
Their sandwiches are delicious!
Big sandwiches, even bigger salads.
Very friendly staff, they let me sample the salami to ensure it wasn’t too spicy. The paninis are great and the coconut macaroons are to die for!

Juliet's is one of downtown's best kept secrets and I think the reason why it's kept so secret is due to the wait caused by so many people, make sure to have at least 30 minutes for lunch otherwise I'd recommend grabbing a bite somewhere else.
Best sandwiches in Frederick and amazing gelato!
Incredible deli meats and a lovely atmosphere
Juliet's has the best California panini in Frederick. The food is always good, fresh and delicious.
Great panini's and affordable!!

I've been here on several occasions and still go sometimes.  Small, cramped and crowded.  It's too small for all they're trying to do.  The hot sandwiches and paninis are very good and their frozen food is great to take home for dinner.  The gelato is not very good and their cold sandwiches tend to taste like they've used cheap cold cuts.
Muffaletta for the win.
The best Italian sandwich in Maryland if not the country. I'm not joking or exaggerating in any way.

Been grabbing lunch here in Downtown Frederick for years.  Their sandwiches are quite good.  Prosciutto & mozzarella for me with a bad of chips, but they have plenty of options.  I hear their homemade tuna salad is also very nice.
Very authentic
Lovely, quaint authentic food small interior limited seating, worth the visit.
Very quaint little cafe. Food was very delicious. Would highly recommend it if you want a little slice of heaven.

These are some of the best sandwiches and subs in Frederick, possibly all of Maryland. The meatball sub (only available on Friday in limited quantities) will change your life. It's probably big enough for two people to share ... although you might not want to.

Legit best panini sandwiches I've ever had. The people complaining about the wait do not understand that high quality food does not take a couple of minutes. I've been going there once a week the past 2-3 months. If anything, based on the quality, it's very fast. On average, a panini sandwich takes about 10 minutes (depending on how busy it is). I'd wait 45 minutes based on how good they are. My only complaint is that there is only 1 Juliet's Italian Market and they are not open 24x7 :) Juliet is awesome!

Amazing prices considering the huge size of the subs. I got the prosciutto and mozzarella sandwich, it was so good, I definitely plan on going back for another one soon. The mozzarella is homemade and it's perfect, next time I'm there I plan on getting a whole ball of it to buy and take home!

We went here after seeing other reviews and are glad we did! It was a Friday so I ordered the meatball sandwich (available only on Friday) and it was worth it, the meatballs are delicious. My daughter got the Prosciutto and Mozzarella and loved it.  I did try a piece of their homemade mozzarella and it was so good! The staff was also extremely nice 👍🏻 Well definitely go back.
Super slow service, small sandwiches, and pricey. Avoid it.

Thank you, Juliet's, for standing the test of time in awesome downtown Frederick (DTF) and for giving our community a taste and feel of little Italy. Your Cannoli is fabulous and a must try and your cookies (especially the macaroon) are out of this world!
Had an excellent California panini from here tonight. Huge sandwich, great value. Desserts are pretty good as well!
Great little italian shop. Paninis are delicious!
My wife and I really enjoy this place.  She seeks this place out for the caprese sandwich.
I had the Muffaletta sub and it was really delicious!  I'll be back!

Easily the best prosciutto and mozzarella sandwich I've had, and the customer service was wonderful. The store is tiny but filled with great products. In addition to my sandwich, I picked up some fresh smoked mozarella and salami for a dinner. It was a little pricy, but so far it promises to be worth it!
Great service and a lovely variety of Italian sundries.
Great subs and selection
Great subs

What a quaint little place! I am unfamiliar with the area and was a little nervous to venture out, but it was easy to find and there is metered parking right out front.  They were so polite and welcoming and it smelled great in there.  It had such an authentic air about it I highly recommend.
5 star panini sandwiches. Customer experience is not great though -- go when it's slow if you can.
Best sandwiches in Frederick
So so goood! I ordered a panini. Turkey with guacamole and mozzarella. The cheese and bread is amazing. Hey make the mozzarella there! The gelato was some of the best I've ever had 💙
Great specials, everyone was super helpful. Blue Cheese pasta salad was awesome.
Delicious Sandwiches
Best sandwiches on the strip as long as you are willing to wait. I absolutely love this place.
Great sandwich. Cozy store!
Best tuna sub in the world!
Great little Italian market and deli!

The prices are a tiny bit steep but the quality of food makes it well worth it. Looking for authentic imported Italian goods look to further they have it all. They even make their own mozzarella. There is a small eat in area, the overall store is as close to an Italian café as you can get without going to Italy.
Amazing service, delicious food, just incredible!!
Absolutely amazing! Wonderful service and wonderful people!

Great tasting sandwiches at great affordable prices. I truly believe that this place serves the best sandwiches in Downtown Frederick. The bread is fresh every day and so are their meats and cheeses. It is just unfortunate that they are located in the middle of the block on a not so busy walking area. This place would put Crabapple (other sandwich shop) out of business should they had a "corner" location with the same size that Crabapple has. Juliet's Italian Market also serves other items too. You should try her homemade lasagna that she freezes for you to take home and cook - "WOW!"
Great food, service was a little slow, but they are a busy place!

Staff was kind of rude when asking about what comes on a sandwich.  The atmosphere was "you should already have known what you wanted before you got here..." so I just left.  There were other customers who were treated differ early, but they seemed to be frequent shoppers.  I'd say it was just that particular staff that made the atmosphere like that, but then again it can be company the business keeps too.

Juliets is one of the best Italian Markets in the area and beyond! The food is always fresh and delicious. I wish she could find a bigger space so that we could go there for dinner too! Juliet herself is  a hard working dedicated person and she is always very friendly and most accommodating. If you haven't been here it is your loss!

To me this is a hidden gem in Frederick. Hand made panini's that are well worth it for lunch. Also if you like to cook as close to authentic Italian food as possible they have some nice exported selections ranging from pasta, sauce and even home made recipes you can take home. The only issue I can say is that if you want to eat there they have limited seating.
My boyfriend and I are Frederick locals and we love and adore this place. Great sandwiches and unique beverages available.
amazing sandwhiches, and make plans for Friday's meatball subs (yum)
Small Italian market with all of the classic Italian foods. Friendly and inviting atmosphere.
I love Juliet's. Their grilled subs are the best. Call ahead and order if it's around lunch time, or you may have to wait a bit. Customer service is always great, and the food is always fresh!

This little Italian market is now called Juliet's. This is my favoriate place to grab luch in Frederick, their food is excellent and the prices are very fair. They have great sandwiches and a good selection of deli salads and such. Everything is really fresh and they make it right in front of you. Juliet's food  is better than most of the high end restaurants in Frederick. I highly recommend.
